Three persons died yesterday in a road crash on Okigwe Road in Aba North council of Abia State. The accident involved a white Mercedes Benz and a black GLK 350 4Matic, which collided, The Nation learnt. Sources said the accident happened about 2am, adding that two persons died on the spot, while the third died at a private hospital where he was taken for medical attention. The sources blamed the accident on speeding. Other passengers were injured, they said. A resident, who gave his name as Chibueze Ogbodo, said, “The accident happened around midnight, about 2am. The bang was too loud that we thought that a bomb may have exploded.”   3,000 Yoruba displaced in Akwa Ibom crisis     NDLEA arrests suspect behind N3b Tramadol linked to Abba…     Chidinma’s trial stalled over Ataga’s bank accounts row   “Knowing the security challenge in the country and issues of gunmen in the southeast and activities of the security operatives, we didn’t want to come out immediately. “When it became obvious that it had nothing to do with gunmen or armed robbery, we came out only to behold bodies of the victims on the road. “Some came out unhurt, others sustained degrees of injuries. Two persons were confirmed dead on the spot, while the other person was said to have died at the hospital. “The driver of the third car, a Lexus SUV, was at top speed and when he saw the accident suddenly, in an attempt to dodge the cars, he lost control of his car and hit the pole in front of the bungalow near the accident scene.” “You know that this road is always busy. If the accident had happened in the day time, it could have been worse than what we have seen here. “Drivers of the three cars were coming back from night clubs and might have been driving under the influence.”